column4:
'If you never do anything, you never become anyone.'
An Education (2009)

'A deer has to be taken with one shot. I try to tell people that but they don't listen.'
The Deer Hunter (1978)

'Will You Come With Me?’
Under the Skin (2013)

'Some nomads are at home everywhere. Others are at home nowhere, and I was one of those'
Tracks (2013)

'You have no idea of the effect you have, do you?' 
Ida (2013)

'I’m trying to write a piece of music that’s about what it feels like to be on the beach with you right now. … I think you captured it.'
Her (2013)

'Love alters not with its brief hours and weeks.'
Only Lovers Left Alive (2013)

'For my dearest darling, treasured, cherished Agatha whom I worship. With respect, adoration, admiration, kisses, gratitude, best wishes, and love from Z to A.'
The Grand Budapest Hotel (2014)

'We were escorted through a green baize door, down a narrow service corridor and into the butlers pantry'
The Grand Budapest Hotel (2014)

'Do we have a kill order?'
Serenity (2005)

'I know, we're all gonna die. Everybody knows that. But I'm going to die today. Funny that… you know, to know' 
Gravity (2013)

'How do I know if I'm dreaming?'
The Congress (2013)

'Where? Which way?'
Starman (1984)

'Why didn't somebody tell me he had one of those… things?'
Batman (1989)

'Ancient ocean, I lack the power to continue, I feel the moment has come to return to the brutal land of men. Let us make a supreme effort and, conscious of our duty, fulfil our destiny on this earth.'
Weekend (1967)

'I want you to move towards me slowly.’
Fish Tank (2009)

'The past is just a story we tell ourselves.'
Her (2013)

'When was the last time you were alone? You can't remember, can you? So please do. Take your time.'
Snowpiercer (2013)

'This town is full of live ones.'
Tron (1982)

'The world changes, we do not, there lies the irony that finally kills us.'
Interview With The Vampire (1994)

'I was going to be a stand-up comedian.'
Planet Terror (2007)

'Life's a bitch and then you die.' 

Fish Tank (2009)

'This great evil. Where does it come from? How'd it steal into the world? What seed, what root did it grow from? Who's doin' this? Who's killin' us? Robbing us of life and light. Mockin' us with the sight of what we might've known.'
The Thin Red Line (1998)

'Jupiter and beyond the infinite'
2001: A Space Odyssey (1968)

'Your story is so beautiful, Curtis. But I don't want to open the door. You know what I want? I want to open a door. … The one that leads to the outside.'
Snowpiercer (2013)

'I hate you. … He can't hear you, you know.'
Dogma (1999)

column1: Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back
column4:
'The force is with you, young Skywalker, but you are not a Jedi yet.'
Star Wars: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back (1980)

'On the other side of the screen, it all looks so easy.'
Tron (1982)

'The site is supposed to be located on an Indian burial ground, and I believe they actually had to repel a few Indian attacks as they were building it.'
The Shining (1980)

'So beautiful. … Endangered.'
The American (2010)

'Free winds and no tyranny for you, Freddie, sailor of the seas. You pay no rent, free to go where you please. Then go, go to that landless latitude and good luck. If you figure a way to live without serving a master, any master, then let the rest of us know, will you? For you'd be the first in the history of the world.' 
The Master (2012)

'To change oneself. My trouble is laziness.'
Persona (1966)

'I made up my mind to resort to more extreme measures.' 
Gattaca (1997)

column1: The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou
column4:
'Sorry about that. You caught me with one foot off the merry-go-round tonight.'
The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou (2004)

'Since the last games, something is different. I can see it. … What can you see? … Hope.' 
The Hunger Games: Catching Fire (2013)

'Sometimes it's good to do what you're supposed to do when you're supposed to do it.'
Frances Ha (2012)

'Every night I come to the same place and wait till the sky catches up with my mood.'
Submarine (2010)

'One can't just leave.'
The Third Man (1949)

'Only those prepared to die will find eternal life.'
Byzantium (2013)

column1: Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind
column4:
'Who made such a terrible mess of the world?'
Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind (1984)

'Help each other. Love everyone. Every leaf. Every ray of light. Forgive.'
The Tree of Life (2011)

'Not very sporting to fire on an unarmed opponent. I thought you were supposed to be good. Aren't you the “good” man? C'mon, Deckard. Show me what you're made of.'
Blade Runner (1982)

'Keep your mind clear. And that’s it. You will have peace of mind. My dear, don’t worry. Learn to adjust yourself.’
Another Earth (2011)

'We stood facing each other for a long time, neither of us made a move, while our battle unfolded in the depths of our minds.'
Hero (2002)

'I'm not mad. I don't want to die. There's someone within me and she says I must die.'
Vertigo (1958)

'Maybe it’s impossible for a man like you to understand. But having a respect for my life, a desire for freedom, and an unyielding love for that belief means I can see past any doubts I may have. Putting my life on the line is not just the only thing I can do, Dom. It’s the right thing.'
Hunger (2008)

'I wish my life could be more like American soap operas. Then, whenever things got dramatic, you could just fade the picture down and pick things up later.'
Submarine (2010)

'So you were in Vietnam? … Yeah. … Were you in the shit? … Yeah, I was in the shit.'
Rushmore (1998)

'Spring break forever.'
Spring Breakers (2012)

'How long was I asleep?'
The Hunger Games (2012)

'What's this war in the heart of nature? Why does nature vie with itself? The land contend with the sea? Is there an avenging power in nature? Not one power, but two?'
The Thin Red Line (1998)

'Snow knew I had been rootless since childhood living nowhere and everywhere. She often said to me, once we had succeeded in killing the king, she would take me back to her home. She said no swords existed there, and no swordsman. There would be only a man and a woman.'
Hero (2002)

column1: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
column4:
'Look where we are!'
Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)

'Jordana hates any place that could be termed romantic. With this in mind, I took her to one of my favourite industrial estates, for some quality one-on-one time.'
Submarine (2010)

'You never seemed to be waiting for me… but we kept meeting at every turn in the path, behind every shrub, at the foot of every statue, at the edge of every fountain. It was as if in that entire garden there were only you and me.'
L’année dernière à Marienbad (1961)

'Listen.'
La Dolce Vita (1960)

‘The survivors of the nuclear fire called the war Judgment Day. They lived only to face a new nightmare: the war against the machines.’
Terminator 2: Judgment Day (1991)

'Marla… the little scratch on the roof of your mouth that would heal if only you could stop tonguing it, but you can't.'
Fight Club (1999)

'Hi, can I tell you something? … Sure, anything you like.'
Paris, Texas (1984)

'Since you wish to die, I will assist you.'
Hero (2002)

'What world is this?… What kingdom?… What shores of what worlds?'
Girl, Interrupted (1999)

'Oh, look. I just found the time machine. The time machine is here. And it works.'
The Science of Sleep (2006)

'I'm a normal girl.' 
Before My Heart Falls (2012)
Made for Pluk de Nacht Festival

'I'm just paying my dues.' 
California is A Place: Superman (2010) 
Made for Pluk de Nacht Festival

'One of these days, Carmina is going to explode.'
Carmina or Blow Up (2012)
Made for Pluk de Nacht Festival

'So how was your trip home? … Uneventful.' 
Wild Bill (2011)
Made for Pluk de Nacht Festival

'Not funny!' 
The We And The I (2012)
Made for Pluk de Nacht festival

'Welcome to The Suck.'
Jarhead (2005)

'This is me. Just as a flower does not choose its color, we are not responsible for what we have come to be. Only once you realize this do you become free, and to become adult is to become free.' 
Stoker (2013)

'Dearest Cecilia. The story can resume.' 
Atonement (2007)

'Please come home with me.' 
Spring Breakers (2012)

'A warrior's ultimate act is to lay down his sword.' 
Hero (2002)

'Do you know if Shell Beach is around here?'
Dark City (1998)

'I might never see you again. I need to tell you where it is.'
Trance (2013)

'I'm here'
Punch-Drunk Love (2002)

'Where are you going? … To ask for directions.'

Hellboy (2004)

'I think I have to make a decision.'
Lola Rennt (1998)

'These are hard times for dreamers.' 
Le fabuleux destin d’Amélie Poulain (2001)

'Somebody like you could really make things all right for me'
Requiem for a Dream (2000)

'What do you think is the best, a game you think you can finish, but never do, or a game that seems impossible to win, but isn't?'
Avalon (2001)

'I just don't know what I'm supposed to be.'
Lost in Translation (2003)

column1: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
column4:
'I don't think we could have asked for a more beautiful evening, do you?'
Close Encounters of the Third Kind (1977)

'Sometimes to create, one must first destroy.'
Prometheus (2012)

'Letting everyone down would be my greatest unhappiness.'
Marie Antoinette (2006)

'Hold my hand. Close your eyes.'
Melancholia (2011)

'Okay, this is where I don't want to be.'
Iron Man (2008)

'What are we doing? Where are we going, home? … Yeah, home.'
Upstream Color (2013)

'Look at this Cod. I love it. God help me I do love it so. I love it more than my life.'
Patton (1970)

'No one will know my secret.'
Death Note (2006)

column1: Twin Peaks: Fire Walk with Me
column4:
'Where are you going, Laura? … Nowhere… fast. And you're not coming.'

Twin Peaks: Fire Walk with Me (1992)

'For a limited time only, Glamour Shots by Deb are 75% off.’
Napoleon Dynamite (2004)

'Happy Birthday, Samantha. Make a wish. … It already came true.'
Sixteen Candles (1984)

'There's a whole ocean of oil under our feet! No one can get at it except for me!'
There Will Be Blood (2007)
Un chien andalou (1929)

'I'd be lost without the weight of you two on my back. I ain't goin' anywhere.'
Winter’s Bone (2010)

'What are we doing here?' 
Sedmikrásky (1966)

'You'll never leave me? … Of course I won't … Of course? … Yes, of course'
Pierrot le fou (1965)

'The city looks so peaceful from up here. … Anything is peaceful from one thousand, three hundred and fifty-three feet.’
Ferris Bueller’s Day Off (1986)

'Your fear of capture and imprisonment is from millions of years ago. You are not there. You are asleep.'
The Master (2012)

'The pills come from a girlfriend who's a shrink, she tried to analyze me once but she got too scared'.
Sin City (2005)

'I'm trying to free your mind, Neo. But I can only show you the door. You're the one that has to walk through it.'
The Matrix (1999)

'Are you looking for shells too? … No, I’m just looking.’
Dr. No (1962)

'The nuns taught us there were two ways through life - the way of nature and the way of grace. You have to choose which one you'll follow.'
The Tree of Life (2011)

'You oughta spend a little more time dealing with yourself, a little less time worrying about what your brother does.'
Ferris Bueller’s Day Off (1986)

'Turn them black. What color are my eyes? … Black … Very good.'
The Master (2012)

'Do you see what comes of all this running around, Mr. Bond? All this jumping and fighting, it's exhausting!' 
Skyfall (2012)

‘Everything is beautiful. You only have to take an interest in things to see their beauty’
Vivre sa vie (1962)

'Infrared. Markers detected'
Holy Motors (2012)

'Are you going to kill me now? … I killed you 10 minutes ago.’
V for Vendetta (2005)

'The whole world's comin' to an end, Mal!'
Natural Born Killers (1994)

'Why are you wearing that stupid bunny suit? … Why are you wearing that stupid man suit?’
Donnie Darko (2001)

'Lawrence, only two kinds of creature get fun in the desert: Bedouins and gods, and you're neither. Take it from me, for ordinary men, it's a burning, fiery furnace.' 
Lawrence of Arabia (1962)

'Joan Jett. The rock 'n' roll heart, street tough brunette.'
The Runaways (2010)

'I hope that whoever you are, you escape this place. I hope that the worlds turns, and that things get better. But what I hope most of all is that you understand what I mean when I tell you that, even though I do not know you, and even though I may never meet you, laugh with you, cry with you, or kiss you, I love you. With all my heart, I love you. Valerie.'
V for Vendetta (2005)

'Incendiary.'
Dredd (2012)

'You can't take that thing out with a plough or something? … Uh-huh.’ 
Looper (2012)

'I think I need everyone to think I'm the greatest, the “Fantastic” Mr. Fox.'
Fantastic Mr. Fox (2009)

'I feel like I can take out the world.' 
Akira (1988)

'If you want me to cancel your evening, I can. … Don't be ridiculous, why would we do that?'
The Devil Wears Prada (2006)

'I am The Gatekeeper!' 
Ghostbusters (1984)

'Alright. Hey. Alright. Good job, guys. Let's just not come in tomorrow. Let's just take a day. Have you ever tried shawarma? There's a shawarma joint about two blocks from here. I don't know what it is, but I wanna try it.'
The Avengers (2012)

'Hi Milton. What's happening? I'm gonna have to ask you to go ahead and move your desk again.'
Office Space (1999)

'I blow that tunnel open, I'm gone. … There’s more to you than that.’
The Dark Knight Rises (2012)

'The mission has been updated'
Safety Not Guaranteed (2012)

'You Maniacs! You blew it up! Ah, damn you! God damn you all to hell!' 
Planet of the Apes (1968)
Le Voyage dans la Lune (1902)

'Get in'
The Matrix (1999)

'I don't like the snappy attitude. This is the most important decision you've made in your lives. Go over by that trampoline and talk it through before you give me another quick answer.'
Moonrise Kingdom (2012)

"Come out to the coast, we’ll get together, have a few laughs…"
Die Hard (1988)

'Come back. Come back to me.'
Atonement (2007)

'I'm a goddamn Peach!'
A League of Their Own (1992)

'When the child was a child, it walked with its arms swinging. It wanted the stream to be a river, the river a torrent, and this puddle to be the sea. When the child was a child, it didn't know it was a child. Everything was full of life, and all life was one. When the child was a child, it had no opinion about anything, no habits. It often sat cross-legged, took off running, had a cowlick in its hair, and didn't make faces when photographed.'
Der Himmel über Berlin (1987)

'I'm not doing anything this weekend… If you want a ride or something?'
Drive (2011)

'A beginning is a very delicate time. Know then, that is is the year 10191.'
Dune (1984)

'This is our land!'
Moonrise Kingdom (2012)

‘My prostate is asymmetrical.’
Cosmopolis (2012)

'We're not bad people. We just come from a bad place.' 
Shame (2011)

'How sexy am I now, huh? Flirty boy! How sexy am I now? … You made my shitlist!’
Natural Born Killers (1994)

'Let's never come here again because it would never be as much fun.' 
Lost in Translation (2003)

'Is life always this hard, or is it just when you're a kid? … Always like this.'
Léon (1994)

'Are you Totoro?'
My Neighbor Totoro (1988)

'What are you doing up so late? … I'm counting the stars … Do you really know all their names? … Yes I do … How many did you count? … A hundred … There are more than a hundred … I know … Why did you stop? … A hundred is enough, once you've counted a hundred all the other hundreds are the same'
Drowning By Numbers (1988)

’Nothing. No matches on prints, DNA, dental. Clothing is custom, no labels. Nothing in his pockets but knives and lint. No name, no other alias.’ 
The Dark Knight (2008)

'He's not a man - a machine. A Terminator. A Cyberdyne Systems Model 101.' 
The Terminator (1984)

'Collecting everything we could of theirs, the Lisbon girls wouldn't leave our minds but they were slipping away. The color of their eyes was fading along with the exact locations… of moles and dimples. From five, they had become four, and they were all the living and the dead, becoming shadows. We would have lost them completely if the girls hadn't contacted us.'
The Virgin Suicides (1999)

'He's our guy.'
10 Things I Hate About You (1999)

'Toto, I've a feeling we're not in Kansas any more.'
The Wizard of Oz (1939)

"You just get here as quick as you can. …  I’ll try. Keep your eyes open. … I haven’t shut my eyes since you were born.”
Haywire (2011)

'It seems that envy is my sin.'
Se7en (1995)

'Are you cool? … I'm cool.'
Reservoir Dogs (1992)

'The sensation you are feeling is the quickening.'
Highlander (1986)

'Dear Mr. Vernon, we accept the fact that we had to sacrifice a whole Saturday in detention for whatever it was we did wrong. What we did *was* wrong. But we think you're crazy to make an essay telling you who we think we are. You see us as you want to see us… In the simplest terms, in the most convenient definitions. But what we found out is that each one of us is a brain. … and an athlete. … and a basket case. … a princess. … and a criminal. … Does that answer your question? … Sincerely yours, the Breakfast Club.’ 
The Breakfast Club (1985)

"If a technological feat is possible, man will do it. Almost as if it’s wired into the core of our being."
Ghost in the Shell (1995)

"Go-Go, I know you feel you must protect your mistress. But I beg you, walk away."
Kill Bill: Vol. 1 (2003)

'Two lives left. I think I'll save one for next Christmas.' 
Batman Returns (1992)

'She slept in my coffin at first, curling her little fingers around my hair.'
Interview With The Vampire (1994)

'So, gentlemen, let's discuss the prospect of ending the war tonight.' 
Inglourious Basterds (2009)

'So this is permanence; love-shattered pride. What once was innocence, has turned on its side.’
Control (2007)

'Take care. Farewell. Camille'
Le Mepris (1963)

'Sidney's more than a mere bass player. He's a fabulous disaster. He's a symbol, a metaphor, he embodies the dementia of a nihilistic generation. He's a fuckin' star.'
Sid and Nancy (1986)

'Fuckin' Quintana… that creep can roll, man. … Yeah, but he’s a pervert, Dude.’
The Big Lebowski (1998)

”Dyson listened while the Terminator laid it all down: Skynet, Judgment Day, the history of things to come. It’s not everyday you find out that you’re responsible for 3 billion deaths. He took it pretty well.’ 
Terminator 2: Judgment Day (1991)

'The years spent in isolation have not equipped him with the tools necessary to judge right from wrong. He's had no context. He's been completely without guidance. Furthermore, his work - the garden sculptures, hairstyles and so forth - indicate that he's a highly imaginative… uh… character. It seems clear that his awareness of what we call reality is radically underdeveloped.'  
Edward Scissorhands (1990)

'Wow, *the* Batman - or is it just “Batman”? Uh, your choice, of course!' 
Batman Returns (1992)

”What I’m not sure about, is if our lives have been so different from the lives of the people we save. We all complete. Maybe none of us really understand what we’ve lived through, or feel we’ve had enough time.’ 
Never Let Me Go (2010)

'The sea's only gifts are harsh blows, and occasionally the chance to feel strong. Now I don't know much about the sea, but I do know that that's the way it is here. And I also know how important it is in life not necessarily to be strong but to feel strong. To measure yourself at least once. To find yourself at least once in the most ancient of human conditions. Facing the blind death stone alone, with nothing to help you but your hands and your own head.'
Into the Wild (2007)

'The Photo Guy at the one hour place? Well, we really don't know that much about him, do we? He might even have a lot of friends. He probably has a girlfriend and a mommy and daddy, who love him. … I don’t think he does.’ 
One Hour Photo (2002)

'I wish I could go with you. … I should kidnap you.’
Marie Antoinette (2006)

'How did you know my name was Chihiro? … I have known you since you were very small.’ 
Spirited Away (2001)

'The Joker planned to be caught.'
The Dark Knight (2008)

'You're incredible Calcifer. Your magic's first class!'
Howl’s Moving Castle (2004)

‘Don’t let yourself get attached to anything you are not willing to walk out on in 30 seconds flat if you feel the heat around the corner.’
Heat (1995)

'You are not born of man. It was the moon that bore you'
Pan’s Labyrinth (2006)

'The statue seemed to move, but didn't. The world had changed, yet stayed the same. I was a newborn vampire weeping at the beauty of the night.'
Interview with the Vampire (1994)

column1: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
column4:
‘She’s different. …  In what way? … In every way.’
The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo (2011)

'Los Angeles November, 2019'
Blade Runner (1982)

'You can't stay in here all day dreaming about heroin and Ziggy Pop.'
Trainspotting (1996)

‘I feel like I’ve been in a coma for the past twenty years. And I’m just now waking up.’
American Beauty (1999)

'What are you? Some sort of angel visiting me from one of my drunk fantasies? How can you be so good?'
Leaving Las Vegas (1995)

'Can I buy you a drink?'
Out of Sight (1998)

'Father… father, the sleeper has awakened!'
Dune (1984)

'I haven't sung for a very long time. But I'll do it tonight, and see how it goes.'
Volver (2006)

'Are you sure he won't mind? … Uli doesn't care about anything. He's a Nihilist. … Ah, that must be exhausting.'
The Big Lebowski (1998)

column1: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
column4:
'How long could we maintain? I wondered. How long until one of us starts raving and jabbering at this boy? What will he think then? This same lonely desert was the last known home of the Manson family; will he make that grim connection when my attorney starts screaming about bats and huge manta rays coming down on the car? If so, well, we'll just have to cut his head off and bury him somewhere, 'cause it goes without saying that we can't turn him loose. He'd report us at once to some kind of outback Nazi law enforcement agency and they'll run us down like dogs. Jesus, did I say that? Or just think it? Was I talking? Did they hear me?'
Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas (1998)

'Once you've met someone you never really forget them. It just takes a while for your memories to return.' 
Spirited Away (2001)

'I made you something. It's a shirt. … Thats… That’s good, thank you. … Will you try it on now? … Now? … Well, in case I have to fix it before you leave again and we don’t see you for another nine years. I wanna make sure it fits.’
Garden State (2004)

'The thought of busting Batman makes me feel all… dirty. Maybe I'll just give myself a bath right here.'
Batman Returns (1992)

‘This city is afraid of me. I have seen its true face. The streets are extended gutters and the gutters are full of blood and when the drains finally scab over, all the vermin will drown. The accumulated filth of all their sex and murder will foam up about their waists and all the whores and politicians will look up and shout: Save us!… and I’ll whisper: no.’
Watchmen (2009)

'Hit harder than you dare, then they'll stop. … What if…? … Then i'll help you. I can do that'
Let the Right One In (2008)

'How do you know he's still alive? I don't know, not for sure, but I believe he is.'
Edward Scissorhands (1990)

'Introduce a little anarchy. Upset the established order, and everything becomes chaos. I'm an agent of chaos. Oh, and you know the thing about chaos? It's fair!' 
The Dark Knight (2008)

'If I drive for you, you give me a time and a place. I give you a five-minute window, anything happens in that five minutes and I'm yours no matter what. I don't sit in while you're running it down; I don't carry a gun… I drive.'
Drive (2011)

'I wish we could sleep'
Lost in Translation (2003)

'Existence. Well, what does it matter? I exist on the best terms I can. The past is now part of my future. The present is well out of hand.'
Control (2007)

'Isn't that the most beautiful thing you have ever seen?'
Marie Antoinette (2006)

'Restate my assumptions: One, Mathematics is the language of nature. Two, Everything around us can be represented and understood through numbers. Three: If you graph the numbers of any system, patterns emerge. Therefore, there are patterns everywhere in nature. Evidence: The cycling of disease epidemics;the wax and wane of caribou populations; sun spot cycles; the rise and fall of the Nile. So, what about the stock market? The universe of numbers that represents the global economy. Millions of hands at work, billions of minds. A vast network, screaming with life. An organism. A natural organism. My hypothesis: Within the stock market, there is a pattern as well… Right in front of me… hiding behind the numbers. Always has been.'
Pi (1998)

'Do you believe in time travel?'
Donnie Darko (2001)

'I have watched you for days. You are everything a man could ever want. It's not just your face, your…figure or your voice. It's your eyes, all the things I see in your eyes.'
Sin City (2005)

'You are beautiful. You're the most beautiful girl in the world. You are my dream.' 
Requiem For A Dream (2000)

'You just sit here and wait for crime to happen?'
SUPER (2010)

'It was a really awful day. I know, I made sure of it. So pick up the cookie, dip it in the milk, and eat it.'  
Stranger Than Fiction (2006)

'Shut her down'
Resident Evil: Exctinction (2007)

'The more one talks, the less the words mean.'
Vivre Sa Vie (1962)

'Sleep, now'
Dark City (1998)

'Dick Laurent is dead…'
Lost Highway (1997)

'Listen, and understand. That terminator is out there. It can't be bargained with. It can't be reasoned with. It doesn't feel pity, or remorse, or fear. And it absolutely will not stop, ever, until you are dead.'
The Terminator (1984)
